<br>
Nathsar Arms (chardok drop, 8 ac 4 wis/dex/agi 2 sv cold/disease, 1k max)<br>
Kromrif Military Leggings (quest in the GD area, 14 ac 6 str 5 wis 5 sv disease/cold, no drop)<br>
Tattered Hide Cloak (Fungus grove drop from Dregs I think, 9 ac 6 sta/wis 55 hp/mana, paid 4k for mine, but down to 3k or less nowadays it seems)<br>
Nearly any other gloves, Grey Flesh (drop in the Grey, 6 ac 6 wis/int 10 dex  20 hp/mana 10 sv cold, paid 2500 for mine but that was cheap, seem to be 3k avg), Coldain Skin (some velious quest, 12 ac 6 wis/int 9 sta 20 hp/mana, 2500-3k avg), even something like gnome skin or split paw gloves would give more wis.<br>
<br>
The key is though that you really want to maximize mana pool, not wis, even though saying &quot;I've got 255 wis&quot; sounds nice, it's nothing but bragging rights if you could have 188 wis with +800 mana.  In this vein, you'd actually be better off with lower wis if you swap out a few items for ones with +mana, such as the earring of twisted leaves (chardok drop, 1 wis 35 hp/mana, 1k ), earring of woven bark (chardok drop, 35 hp/mana, 1k), Shadel Bandit ring (fungus grove drop, 55 hp/mana 10 sv disease 5 sv cold, 4k), Supple Scale armband (KC drop, 5 wis/int 25 mana 10 sv fire, no drop) <p>Aluaeia
<br>Level 53 Fier`dal Wanderer of Tunare
<br>Tarew Marr
